President Obama spoke with Spanish President Jose Luis Zapatero and Italian Prime Minister Silvio Berlusconi regarding the eurozone crisis. They discussed the economic challenges faced by Spain and Italy and their efforts to improve competitiveness. The leaders also condemned the Assad regime's use of violence in Syria and agreed to consult on further measures to pressure the regime and support the Syrian people's democratic aspirations. Additionally, President Zapatero and Prime Minister Berlusconi expressed condolences for the deaths of 30 American servicemen in Afghanistan, and President Obama highlighted the strength of the coalition in Afghanistan.